rComments: Super easy class as long as you have a good partner. Follow her rubric and instructions religiously, she posts examples in her slides - use these as templates for your assignments and you will be guaranteed an easy A+. Make sure your topic is smt that you feel comfy working w the entire semester. Was super chill class with not that much work!
Absolutely horrible. Avoid. I get A+ always but she made me get A-. Very bad marking and really hard assignment the whole class was based on just group work. Avoid her.
It became somehow a strange class during the pandemic. If you put effort into the assignments and meet her rubric requirements, you should be fine. She gives many examples in class
I am definitely not interested in public health. However, Dr. Pilutti made this class interesting and doable!

UMM miss gurl marks based on her mood, she expects us to read her mind and its like her rubric is there for fun. No exams just long soul sucking assignments, I think she forgets this is an undergrad class. dont take her

1) not a good presenter or lecturer. Says 'um' after every other word to the point where i dont even know what her point is. She uploads transcripts of her lectures and i can prove the amount of times she says 'um'. 2) horrible grading scheme. she grades based on arbitrary measures so you will never know if you're gonna do well or not. just NO
She's straightforward about her expectations and very fair with marking.
Amazing class and amazing prof. Lectures are clear and informative, evaluations are exactly what you'd expect, and the content is interesting

rComments: The entire course she teaches is pointless, from start to finish. No one in their right mind would enjoy it and her teaching style does her reputation no favours. There is nothing interesting about her course and the students are often confused at what they are even supposed to study.

Course was ok, study the slides. If you go to class, she'll go over the readings, and you'll have some answers ready for the exams (which include some short answer) Big group project instead of final exam, which was pretty straightforward. She seems to really want to engage with students, so there's lots of discussion time in class.

It is a new course at uOttawa so it is not perfectly structured. However, she was able to make the material interesting and instead of a final exam, we had to create a health promotion campaign in groups. She gave good feedback and was responsive when asked questions. Definitely recommend her.
Lara is super nice! Spends a bit more time talking than is necessary, but she's interesting and very reasonable. Easy enough class - definitely take this prof if you can!
